{
  "doc_id": "37919",
  "text": "Another competitive decomposition strategy is delta grouping [CITATION_1] . It measures the amount of change (delta value) in each of the decision variables to identify the interacting variables. The variables with smaller delta values are grouped in one subcomponent. To avoid using fixed subcomponent sizes, an MLCC algorithm [CITATION_2] was proposed. In MLCC a set of possible subcomponent sizes are provided and a proper size value is assigned to each subcomponent according to the performance of using these values during the coevolution. To scale up the CMA-ES to LSO problems, Liu and Tang [CITATION_3] proposed a CC-based CMA-ES, named CC-CMA-ES. A decomposition strategies pool is constructed and used in an adaptive manner to decompose a given problem.",
